directions: [["Preheat oven to 375 degrees and line 8 x 8 baking dish with unbleached parchment paper."],["In a large bowl, add wet ingredients and whisk to combine."],["Add cacao powder, baking soda and salt; whisk until well mixed."],["Give zucchini a gentle squeeze but do not ring out completely, add to a bowl and stir."],["Add flour and mix gently until combined."],["Transfer batter into prepared baking dish and level with spatula. Bake for 25-28 minutes or until the centre is barely jiggly. Do not over bake as brownies will have more of a cake consistency. A toothpick inserted has to come out somewhat not clean."],["Remove from the oven and let cool for about an hour. Lift by the parchment paper flaps and transfer to a cooling rack to cool off completely."],[""],[""],[""]]
notes: Honey or other liquid sweeteners can be substituted for the maple syrup.
